 Appearances (Goals). Mikalay Ryndzyuk (Belarusian:  ; Russian:  ; born 2 February 1978) is a Belarusian footballer, who currently plays for Dinamo Samarqand. Mikalay Ryndzyuk started his career at Smena Minsk. He played the first season at 1994/95 at third level. After he played the first winter league in 1995, he transferred to FC BATE, at that time in third division. His high goal scoring rate helped BATE win promotion to top division in 1997. He then signed by Lokomotiv Moscow in 1998. In summer 1999, he moved back to BATE, and spent 2000 season for FC Lokomotiv Nizhny Novgorod and FC Kristall Smolensk. In November 2000, he was signed by Gaziantepspor, where he signed a deal until summer 2003. But he was away from field since November 2001, and in September 2002, he transferred to Rubin Kazan.[1]
